## Spectograms
### secretaudio.wav
I opened the file in Audacity and viewed the spectogram instead of the wave form and it showed the following:
> super secret message

## Steganography
### stegosteg.jpg
I used steghide with an empty password to extract the contents hidden within the image.
`steghide extract -sf stegosteg.jpg`

This wrote a file containing the following:
> SpaghettiSteg

## Security through obscurity
### Download and get 'inside' the file. What is the first filename & extension?
I ran binwalk on the file to identify its contents and extract them `binwalk -e <meme.jpg>`
This contained a .rar file which when extracted contained a new image called hackerchat.png

A: hackerchat.png

### Get inside the archive and inspect the file carefully. Find the hidden text.
I ran strings on the hackerchat.png using `strings hackerchat.png` and it contains the following that was appended to the end of the file: "AHH_YOU_FOUND_ME!"

A: AHH_YOU_FOUND_ME!
